WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.256 --> 00:00:09.801
["Falling in Love. Falling Apart"
by Peter Groenwald playing]

2
00:00:14.639 --> 00:00:19.144
♪ Or is this just the start ♪

3
00:00:20.937 --> 00:00:25.984
♪ Are we falling in love? ♪

4
00:00:27.527 --> 00:00:31.698
♪ Or are we falling apart ♪

5
00:00:34.534 --> 00:00:40.081
♪ Are we falling in love ♪

6
00:00:41.332 --> 00:00:47.547
♪ Or are we falling apart ♪

7
00:00:47.630 --> 00:00:51.342
-[people chattering]
-[upbeat music playing]

8
00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:59.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

9
00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:11.863
I remember this. Don't tell me.

10
00:01:11.946 --> 00:01:14.157
"Feeling like shit" steak and eggs.

11
00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:16.367
Yep. that's what they're called.

12
00:01:18.745 --> 00:01:20.330
[sighs]

13
00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:22.206
I'm sorry.

14
00:01:22.707 --> 00:01:23.750
For what?

15
00:01:24.334 --> 00:01:27.420
Don't do that. okay?
I didn't know he was coming.

16
00:01:27.504 --> 00:01:31.841
And if he hadn't come.
were you ever going to tell me?

17
00:01:31.925 --> 00:01:35.303
Yeah. I was going to tell you.
But you know what? I didn't have to.

18
00:01:36.721 --> 00:01:37.889
Thanks. Annie.

19
00:01:39.265 --> 00:01:41.059
You threw in the towel.

20
00:01:41.142 --> 00:01:42.185
You did.

21
00:01:43.728 --> 00:01:47.857
We're two adults living different lives.
I was living mine. you were living yours.

22
00:01:47.941 --> 00:01:49.651
My life didn't lead to a ring.

23
00:01:49.734 --> 00:01:51.820
You see me wearing a ring. asshole?

24
00:01:55.240 --> 00:01:56.241
What does that mean?

25
00:01:56.324 --> 00:01:58.368
Means I didn't know what to say.

26
00:01:58.952 --> 00:02:00.495
I still don't know what to say.

27
00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:02.914
I didn't expect this to happen.

28
00:02:02.997 --> 00:02:04.833
That really softens the blow.

29
00:02:04.916 --> 00:02:07.085
How could I forget what a child you are?

30
00:02:07.669 --> 00:02:08.878
You were busy.

31
00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:10.964
[Quinn] Mm.

32
00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:13.800
It's a little creepy. isn't it?

33
00:02:13.883 --> 00:02:17.637
I mean. flying all the way out here
just to profess his love.

34
00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:21.766
It's what you should have done.

35
00:02:23.852 --> 00:02:26.312
[gentle contemplative music playing]

36
00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:34.612
[music stops]

37
00:02:56.926 --> 00:02:58.094
Good morning.

38
00:02:59.929 --> 00:03:01.055
Good morning.

39
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:05.018
I can't believe you're here.

40
00:03:05.685 --> 00:03:06.686
I know.

41
00:03:10.648 --> 00:03:12.650
I just couldn't handle the long distance.

42
00:03:12.734 --> 00:03:13.818
[Quinn chuckles]

43
00:03:13.902 --> 00:03:15.612
We've been apart for 18 hours.

44
00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:19.073
-18 hours of pure agony.
-[chuckles]

45
00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:24.454
Look. I know it's only been…

46
00:03:25.830 --> 00:03:27.790
Six months. but I just…

47
00:03:29.375 --> 00:03:30.460
I just know.

48
00:03:33.171 --> 00:03:34.672
I see our lives together.

49
00:03:38.343 --> 00:03:39.552
In New York.

50
00:03:40.887 --> 00:03:43.473
I can quit the Philharmonic
and become a cowboy.

51
00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:48.102
You on a horse. Good Lord.

52
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:50.230
No. No. no.

53
00:03:51.147 --> 00:03:54.025
-My hands are only good for two things.
-Oh. yeah?

54
00:03:54.108 --> 00:03:55.318
Cello.

55
00:03:55.401 --> 00:03:57.487
-And?
-And. uh…

56
00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:03.201
[gentle contemplative music continues]

57
00:04:06.788 --> 00:04:10.750
Oliver. I'm sorry. I know you probably
pictured last night going differently.

58
00:04:10.833 --> 00:04:13.294
No. hey. It's all right.

59
00:04:14.379 --> 00:04:17.257
You said you needed time. Just… take it.

60
00:04:18.841 --> 00:04:21.052
I don't need an answer until you know.

61
00:04:23.388 --> 00:04:24.389
Okay.

62
00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:27.392
Thank you.

63
00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:28.476
Yeah.

64
00:04:38.444 --> 00:04:39.445
No.

65
00:04:41.197 --> 00:04:43.157
-What?
-I have to go to work.

66
00:04:44.534 --> 00:04:45.952
-Now?
-Mm-hm.

67
00:04:47.704 --> 00:04:50.415
Can we pick this back up a little later?

68
00:04:50.498 --> 00:04:51.624
Absolutely.

69
00:04:57.005 --> 00:04:58.715
You go to work. and…

70
00:04:59.549 --> 00:05:02.218
I'll just be here. in your bed.

71
00:05:03.219 --> 00:05:04.220
Naked.

72
00:05:05.888 --> 00:05:07.432
You're naked under there?

73
00:05:09.892 --> 00:05:11.311
More than just naked.

74
00:05:14.564 --> 00:05:15.690
That is so unfair.

75
00:05:17.775 --> 00:05:18.776
Go on. then.

76
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:20.111
Off to work you go.

77
00:05:24.866 --> 00:05:26.784
[music fades]

78
00:05:31.247 --> 00:05:33.541
Look out! Fancy Yancy.

79
00:05:34.542 --> 00:05:37.920
Oh. don't be so grumpy.
You got played. handsome. It happens.

80
00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:40.882
Easy to lose your edge. isn't it?
A little bun in the oven?

81
00:05:40.965 --> 00:05:42.884
Enough. All right?

82
00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:46.763
You are not getting one brick
of this place. not a curl of dust.

83
00:05:47.388 --> 00:05:50.350
Mm. I think one or two curls
might be coming my way.

84
00:05:51.267 --> 00:05:53.019
I'm not selling this ranch. Sidney.

85
00:05:53.102 --> 00:05:55.772
I don't care what game
you think you won. Not happening.

86
00:05:55.855 --> 00:05:58.149
It wasn't a game. Yancy.

87
00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:00.442
Not to me.

88
00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:02.862
But I'll never be your girl again. will I?

89
00:06:02.945 --> 00:06:06.074
So I guess I will have
to be your nightmare.

90
00:06:06.157 --> 00:06:09.911
The doe-eyed wife who hung around hoping.
only to get cheated on for her troubles.

91
00:06:09.994 --> 00:06:12.246
-Sidney.
-Think a judge won't see it my way?

92
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:15.291
I'm going to the bank. all right?
I'm going right now.

93
00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:18.252
Going to take out a second mortgage
and get your walking away money.

94
00:06:18.336 --> 00:06:21.089
But then… you walk away.

95
00:06:21.172 --> 00:06:22.256
That's the deal.

96
00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:24.926
All right.

97
00:06:26.260 --> 00:06:29.597
All right. But that cash
better stack up to the moon.

98
00:06:34.477 --> 00:06:36.729
I got your nuts in my hand. babe.

99
00:06:36.813 --> 00:06:38.356
Don't make me squeeze.

100
00:06:40.066 --> 00:06:41.359
[door opens]

101
00:06:42.151 --> 00:06:43.027
[door closes]

102
00:06:43.111 --> 00:06:45.154
[Dan] Shit. Damn boots.

103
00:06:45.238 --> 00:06:46.364
[knocking]

104
00:06:46.447 --> 00:06:47.573
[Lauren] Morning. Dad.

105
00:06:47.657 --> 00:06:50.118
Good morning. sweetheart. How'd you sleep?

106
00:06:50.201 --> 00:06:51.411
Not great.

107
00:06:53.788 --> 00:06:54.956
Everything okay?

108
00:06:56.457 --> 00:06:57.583
How's Mom?

109
00:06:58.292 --> 00:07:00.503
Uh. hanging in there. best she can.

110
00:07:00.586 --> 00:07:04.966
Started a book club. got all the inmates
reading something called romantasy.

111
00:07:05.591 --> 00:07:08.553
That's good. I'm happy to hear that.

112
00:07:08.636 --> 00:07:11.055
She would love to see you. you know.

113
00:07:12.056 --> 00:07:13.433
Whenever you're ready.

114
00:07:17.478 --> 00:07:18.521
Are you okay?

115
00:07:20.773 --> 00:07:22.275
Still working through it.

116
00:07:22.942 --> 00:07:23.942
Yeah.

117
00:07:25.611 --> 00:07:27.321
Your mother made her choices.

118
00:07:28.114 --> 00:07:29.115
She did.

119
00:07:30.867 --> 00:07:33.995
Still. I knew how unhappy she was
and how bad she wanted out.

120
00:07:34.787 --> 00:07:37.206
She was something in high school. Lauren.

121
00:07:37.957 --> 00:07:39.500
Had such big dreams.

122
00:07:39.584 --> 00:07:41.919
[melancholic music playing]

123
00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:46.924
Sometimes I think that my sentence
is wondering who she might have been

124
00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:48.301
if I hadn't…

125
00:07:53.848 --> 00:07:56.434
All we can do is look forward. darling.

126
00:07:58.978 --> 00:07:59.979
Yep.

127
00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:01.981
You're right. Dad.

128
00:08:05.067 --> 00:08:07.069
[music fades]

129
00:08:09.697 --> 00:08:11.657
[indistinct chatter]

130
00:08:18.915 --> 00:08:20.333
Why are you parking?

131
00:08:21.959 --> 00:08:24.003
I wanted to tell you before now. but...

132
00:08:24.086 --> 00:08:25.838
You went to Staten behind my back?

133
00:08:26.714 --> 00:08:28.591
-I didn't...
-After I told you not to.

134
00:08:28.674 --> 00:08:31.260
I didn't go to Staten. I went to Sam.

135
00:08:32.136 --> 00:08:35.097
Can we do this later?
I don't want to be late on day one.

136
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:37.767
[quiet dramatic music playing]

137
00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:39.644
[cow mooing]

138
00:08:42.897 --> 00:08:44.357
[music fades]

139
00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:46.692
All this mesquite and shit.
I want it gone.

140
00:08:46.776 --> 00:08:50.655
We'll start here. clear this whole
section. all along the creek bed. okay?

141
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:58.538
All due respect. Senator. that land's
still recovering from pipeline drought.

142
00:08:58.621 --> 00:09:01.791
Tear it up now.
you won't get grass. you'll get dust.

143
00:09:01.874 --> 00:09:05.002
Well. like I said. Jake. call me Sam.

144
00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:08.464
As in. "We're on it. Sam."

145
00:09:12.260 --> 00:09:15.471
I'll gas up the Bobcat.
Probably knock out a dozen acres by dusk.

146
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:17.139
Thank you.

147
00:09:17.223 --> 00:09:19.809
Forget the dust.
That's native pasture in there.

148
00:09:19.892 --> 00:09:22.562
Root plowing will scar the land.
drive out wildlife.

149
00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:24.814
kill any shot for native grass long term.

150
00:09:24.897 --> 00:09:26.148
[Sam] Hm.

151
00:09:26.232 --> 00:09:29.610
Kit. do me a favor.
Put your brother on a leash.

152
00:09:29.694 --> 00:09:30.903
Yes. sir.

153
00:09:32.613 --> 00:09:36.576
In the last few months. I can't shake the
feeling that y'all think you know better.

154
00:09:36.659 --> 00:09:38.452
that Staten knows better.

155
00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:40.663
Well. gone are the days.

156
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:42.748
Kit here is the new blood.

157
00:09:43.332 --> 00:09:44.709
He represents me.

158
00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:47.878
If you want your wages. you remember that.

159
00:09:48.504 --> 00:09:49.589
Remember what?

160
00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:55.094
-Why is the grapple on the skid steer?
-Glad you could make it.

161
00:09:55.177 --> 00:09:56.304
We're reseeding.

162
00:09:56.387 --> 00:09:58.806
Herd's about to get
a lot bigger. [chuckles]

163
00:09:58.889 --> 00:10:00.141
The hell's he doing here?

164
00:10:00.224 --> 00:10:03.019
Well. he's working for me.
Is that a problem?

165
00:10:04.645 --> 00:10:06.063
-Let me talk to you...
-Staten.

166
00:10:07.356 --> 00:10:08.691
Take a lap with me.

167
00:10:09.942 --> 00:10:10.818
Come on. boss.

168
00:10:10.901 --> 00:10:13.487
[quiet dramatic music playing]

169
00:10:23.414 --> 00:10:25.416
[bluesy rock music playing]

170
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:31.714
-Bro!
-[sighs]

171
00:10:31.797 --> 00:10:34.550
Bro! What the hell is going on?

172
00:10:34.634 --> 00:10:37.094
-You're pregnant. for starters.
-Which you knew.

173
00:10:37.178 --> 00:10:38.471
[chuckles] Which I knew.

174
00:10:38.554 --> 00:10:41.682
What I didn't know
was that Britain's sexiest man alive

175
00:10:41.766 --> 00:10:44.602
was flying in
to propose to my best friend.

176
00:10:45.478 --> 00:10:48.147
How's he taking the non-answer?

177
00:10:49.273 --> 00:10:53.110
What? "I need a little time"
is definitely a non-answer.

178
00:10:53.194 --> 00:10:55.821
I do need time. I was being honest.

179
00:10:55.905 --> 00:10:57.281
Oliver's…

180
00:10:58.991 --> 00:11:00.618
Amazing. okay? He is.

181
00:11:01.369 --> 00:11:04.205
And our time in Brooklyn together
was amazing. too.

182
00:11:04.288 --> 00:11:07.875
We played shows together.
We went to jazz clubs at night.

183
00:11:07.958 --> 00:11:11.629
We took the train. ate oysters.

184
00:11:11.712 --> 00:11:15.132
We partied out. like proper partied

185
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:18.636
with poets and painters and…

186
00:11:20.221 --> 00:11:22.264
[sighs]

187
00:11:22.348 --> 00:11:23.849
It was so much fun.

188
00:11:23.933 --> 00:11:27.853
But my heart is here. It always has been.
I told him that. He knew.

189
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:30.106
-And then Staten…
-Mm.

190
00:11:30.189 --> 00:11:31.816
[groans] Staten!

191
00:11:31.899 --> 00:11:35.111
Who. in true to form.
realized what a dipshit he was

192
00:11:35.194 --> 00:11:37.279
and wants another shot. now.

193
00:11:37.363 --> 00:11:39.198
Great. Hot men everywhere.

194
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:40.908
I can't give Oliver an answer.

195
00:11:40.991 --> 00:11:44.954
Not with my mom trying to sell the house.
this town drying up before our eyes...

196
00:11:45.037 --> 00:11:46.706
Okay… Stop.

197
00:11:47.415 --> 00:11:48.582
And breathe.

198
00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:51.210
It's okay.

199
00:11:51.711 --> 00:11:54.380
You're okay.
We're going to figure this out.

200
00:11:55.756 --> 00:11:57.758
I'm supposed to be saying that to you.

201
00:11:57.842 --> 00:12:00.219
Oh. you will. Plenty of time.

202
00:12:04.890 --> 00:12:08.978
Just tell me Yancy's divorcing that girl
before this beautiful baby comes.

203
00:12:09.478 --> 00:12:10.479
I mean.

204
00:12:11.230 --> 00:12:14.066
he's trying. as we speak.

205
00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:16.402
When did Cap buy a plot of land?

206
00:12:16.485 --> 00:12:19.905
Looks like the sale went through
about seven months ago.

207
00:12:19.989 --> 00:12:21.073
A month before he died.

208
00:12:21.157 --> 00:12:26.203
You didn't get any mail. notification
of the refinance. property taxes?

209
00:12:26.287 --> 00:12:30.166
It's possible. There's been so much
estate stuff coming through that I could…

210
00:12:31.625 --> 00:12:33.586
Sorry. did you say property taxes?

211
00:12:33.669 --> 00:12:36.547
You owe six months of back taxes.

212
00:12:41.260 --> 00:12:42.970
[Yancy] Tell me I'm missing something.

213
00:12:44.430 --> 00:12:46.932
Well. if you are. I'm missing it too.

214
00:12:49.143 --> 00:12:52.354
This whole thing is overgrazed. eroded…

215
00:12:52.897 --> 00:12:54.732
It's run dry by that pipeline.

216
00:12:55.775 --> 00:12:56.776
Worthless.

217
00:12:57.485 --> 00:12:58.986
Glass half empty. yeah.

218
00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:05.242
Why would he refinance Fuller
to free up cash and buy this?

219
00:13:05.326 --> 00:13:06.368
I don't know.

220
00:13:07.369 --> 00:13:09.413
I never knew Cap to make a bad investment.

221
00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:12.792
Maybe that tact dulled more
than we even realized.

222
00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:15.211
What are you gonna do?

223
00:13:15.711 --> 00:13:16.712
I don't know.

224
00:13:17.338 --> 00:13:19.673
Start by selling cattle
at the auction tomorrow.

225
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:21.008
Hold on.

226
00:13:21.091 --> 00:13:23.344
-How many?
-Hundred?

227
00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:27.014
Yancy. it's… [clicks teeth]

228
00:13:27.848 --> 00:13:29.350
That's gonna tank you.

229
00:13:29.433 --> 00:13:31.185
What am I supposed to do?

230
00:13:31.727 --> 00:13:34.146
No one but you knows the shit I'm in now.

231
00:13:34.230 --> 00:13:37.566
Sid's got me over a barrel.
I gotta pay her off and get her out.

232
00:13:38.317 --> 00:13:40.694
There's something else
you're not telling me.

233
00:13:46.325 --> 00:13:47.451
Ellie's pregnant.

234
00:13:48.577 --> 00:13:49.829
-Whoa.
-Yeah.

235
00:13:49.912 --> 00:13:51.705
-Okay. [chuckles]
-Yep.

236
00:13:52.331 --> 00:13:53.624
Congratulations.

237
00:13:53.707 --> 00:13:55.167
You're gonna be a daddy.

238
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:57.545
[contemplative music playing]

239
00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:59.046
Thank you. Yeah.

240
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:04.510
I gotta figure this out.

241
00:14:05.094 --> 00:14:06.679
Protect my kid's future.

242
00:14:07.721 --> 00:14:09.807
That's the only thing that matters.

243
00:14:16.355 --> 00:14:18.941
[lively music playing on TV]

244
00:14:22.528 --> 00:14:23.612
What's this?

245
00:14:24.405 --> 00:14:25.531
Love Island.

246
00:14:26.365 --> 00:14:31.036
I mean. it's absolute shit to the UK
version. but… it does the job.

247
00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:32.955
Why are your bags packed?

248
00:14:33.038 --> 00:14:34.707
[inhales deeply] Um…

249
00:14:35.708 --> 00:14:36.917
Because I'm leaving.

250
00:14:41.589 --> 00:14:42.756
Look. I…

251
00:14:44.633 --> 00:14:47.761
I meant everything I said.
and it's all still on the table.

252
00:14:47.845 --> 00:14:49.179
Now. it's all…

253
00:14:49.263 --> 00:14:51.515
It's still very much on the table.

254
00:14:51.599 --> 00:14:54.518
I just… need time to think.

255
00:14:55.352 --> 00:14:57.897
I have the conservatory
in a few weeks. so…

256
00:14:58.397 --> 00:15:02.276
I'm just gonna go back
and pray to the gods of Love Island

257
00:15:02.359 --> 00:15:05.446
that someday very soon
you'll follow me back.

258
00:15:09.158 --> 00:15:11.118
You're not going to New York.

259
00:15:12.578 --> 00:15:13.871
Tickets are booked.

260
00:15:14.914 --> 00:15:16.040
I don't care.

261
00:15:17.625 --> 00:15:18.918
[chuckles faintly]

262
00:15:20.836 --> 00:15:22.838
[gentle guitar music playing]

263
00:15:24.298 --> 00:15:25.883
You have to hear something.

264
00:15:28.844 --> 00:15:31.221
[animal sounds]

265
00:15:38.145 --> 00:15:39.396
[Quinn exhales deeply]

266
00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:44.276
Just listen.

267
00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:46.487
[animal sounds continue]

268
00:15:56.163 --> 00:15:57.539
It's like a symphony.

269
00:15:58.624 --> 00:15:59.875
[Quinn] Mm-hm.

270
00:16:01.377 --> 00:16:02.252
Yeah.

271
00:16:02.336 --> 00:16:05.422
["There Are No Words"
by Andrew Belle playing]

272
00:16:14.139 --> 00:16:17.643
♪ I know it hurts ♪

273
00:16:18.143 --> 00:16:21.438
♪ Good things will end ♪

274
00:16:32.032 --> 00:16:35.119
♪ All things are light ♪

275
00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:39.540
♪ Pure and undignified ♪

276
00:16:49.883 --> 00:16:52.136
["There Are No Words" ends]

277
00:16:59.268 --> 00:17:02.062
-Does this grudge have a timeline?
-Anywhere but Double K.

278
00:17:02.146 --> 00:17:04.023
-You had to go there.
-I looked.

279
00:17:04.106 --> 00:17:05.441
I told you that.

280
00:17:05.524 --> 00:17:08.777
For three damn months
after Davis cashed out. I looked.

281
00:17:08.861 --> 00:17:12.156
You hate me being there.
At least I can keep an eye on you now.

282
00:17:12.239 --> 00:17:13.574
-Keep an eye on me?
-Yes.

283
00:17:13.657 --> 00:17:16.118
Sam was this close
to canning your ass yesterday.

284
00:17:16.201 --> 00:17:17.453
You're welcome.

285
00:17:18.954 --> 00:17:22.541
I need you to cover for me at the auction.
Sam needs a couple hands.

286
00:17:22.624 --> 00:17:25.210
-Hell no. I'm not going.
-Yes. you are.

287
00:17:25.294 --> 00:17:28.797
The man's an idiot! He's going to ruin
Double K like he ruined this town!

288
00:17:28.881 --> 00:17:31.258
-Everything that Staten fought...
-Enough!

289
00:17:32.176 --> 00:17:33.052
Enough.

290
00:17:33.135 --> 00:17:36.180
When are you going to start
looking out for yourself?

291
00:17:36.847 --> 00:17:39.641
I know you look up to Staten. I get it.

292
00:17:39.725 --> 00:17:42.186
But you have to see this thing
for what it is.

293
00:17:42.269 --> 00:17:45.647
Sam Kirkland runs the show. period.

294
00:17:46.398 --> 00:17:49.777
You want to stay on?
You better pick the right side.

295
00:17:50.360 --> 00:17:51.403
Or what?

296
00:17:57.451 --> 00:17:58.660
Where are you going?

297
00:17:58.744 --> 00:18:00.537
I have my own marching orders.

298
00:18:02.998 --> 00:18:04.083
Hi.

299
00:18:04.166 --> 00:18:05.167
Excuse me.

300
00:18:07.419 --> 00:18:08.420
Sorry.

301
00:18:11.548 --> 00:18:12.841
Are you guys okay?

302
00:18:14.259 --> 00:18:19.056
Yeah. it's just that this whole
working together thing isn't working.

303
00:18:19.139 --> 00:18:22.810
But… it's fine. I'm fine.

304
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:25.104
How are you? What's up?

305
00:18:27.773 --> 00:18:30.442
I'm going to go see my mom today.

306
00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:33.362
Wow. today?

307
00:18:33.445 --> 00:18:36.115
Yeah. uh. it's time. Um…

308
00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:40.244
Just want to talk to her
and just get some questions answered.

309
00:18:40.327 --> 00:18:41.578
Of course.

310
00:18:43.872 --> 00:18:45.457
Oh. shit. you want me to come?

311
00:18:45.541 --> 00:18:48.377
No. I mean. I was going to ask.

312
00:18:48.460 --> 00:18:50.838
But no. it's fine. I can do it myself.

313
00:18:51.547 --> 00:18:54.383
Besides. I heard part
of that fight outside.

314
00:18:54.466 --> 00:18:57.136
And I am not going
to get you in trouble at work.

315
00:18:57.219 --> 00:18:59.888
-Fuck work and fuck Kit. I'm coming.
-No. that's...

316
00:18:59.972 --> 00:19:02.933
-Please. no. this is the least I could do.
-Stop. just no. okay?

317
00:19:03.016 --> 00:19:04.017
Just…

318
00:19:06.353 --> 00:19:07.479
Kit is right.

319
00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:11.692
You have to look out for yourself.

320
00:19:11.775 --> 00:19:14.111
[contemplative music playing]

321
00:19:23.370 --> 00:19:25.164
[music stops]

322
00:19:25.747 --> 00:19:28.125
-You going to that auction?
-Yeah. I am.

323
00:19:29.376 --> 00:19:30.544
What's your plan?

324
00:19:31.795 --> 00:19:35.632
Going to buy a shit load of cattle.
turn the Double K into the Four Sixes.

325
00:19:35.716 --> 00:19:37.968
-Hm.
-You'd do it different. huh?

326
00:19:38.051 --> 00:19:39.219
I didn't say that.

327
00:19:39.303 --> 00:19:41.889
Yeah. you did. That shit-eating grin.

328
00:19:42.472 --> 00:19:45.142
Hey. you do what you want. Pops.

329
00:19:45.726 --> 00:19:46.726
Ah.

330
00:19:47.394 --> 00:19:49.521
I hear that Yancy Grey's gotta sell.

331
00:19:49.605 --> 00:19:52.983
That's a shame because I'm going
to get all his cattle for nothing.

332
00:19:53.066 --> 00:19:54.276
No. no. no.

333
00:19:55.068 --> 00:19:56.862
Leave that kid alone. hear me?

334
00:19:56.945 --> 00:19:58.655
I'm asking you.

335
00:19:58.739 --> 00:20:00.741
You knew Cap. He was your friend.

336
00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:03.076
[sighs] I'm not friends with dead men.

337
00:20:05.662 --> 00:20:08.040
Just Kit Russell then. is that it?

338
00:20:08.123 --> 00:20:11.293
How could you let that son of a bitch on
our property? He killed your grandson.

339
00:20:11.376 --> 00:20:12.753
Marge Brigman…

340
00:20:14.254 --> 00:20:15.672
Killed my grandson.

341
00:20:18.759 --> 00:20:19.760
Kit…

342
00:20:21.136 --> 00:20:22.471
He's got a loyalty in him.

343
00:20:22.554 --> 00:20:25.224
-something maybe you don't understand.
-[scoffs]

344
00:20:25.307 --> 00:20:27.726
Now. I'm going to go to this auction.

345
00:20:27.809 --> 00:20:29.478
You should sit this one out.

346
00:20:30.270 --> 00:20:31.271
Take the day.

347
00:20:33.774 --> 00:20:35.567
Think about how you fit in here.

348
00:20:36.777 --> 00:20:38.320
If you can't play ball…

349
00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:41.740
You should go find a hobby.

350
00:20:44.576 --> 00:20:45.702
It's not a hobby.

351
00:20:47.996 --> 00:20:50.040
Find a hobby. I'll find a hobby.

352
00:20:50.540 --> 00:20:53.335
-[cows mooing]
-["Eagle Birds" by The Black Keys playing]

353
00:20:53.418 --> 00:20:55.295
♪ Feel you simmer down ♪

354
00:20:55.921 --> 00:20:57.714
♪ In the pan ♪

355
00:20:58.215 --> 00:21:03.178
♪ Feed me dinner right out
Of your hand ♪

356
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:05.597
♪ Don't nobody wanna be lonely ♪

357
00:21:05.681 --> 00:21:08.558
♪ Everybody oughta be loved sometime ♪

358
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:11.687
♪ So love me right ♪

359
00:21:12.729 --> 00:21:13.897
♪ Woo ♪

360
00:21:15.357 --> 00:21:17.693
[auctioneer] Welcome back.
It's been a doozy of a morning

361
00:21:17.776 --> 00:21:20.112
at the Ransom Canyon Cattle Auction.

362
00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:25.367
And bidding starts at $120. Now. $121
to the gentleman on my right hand.

363
00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:28.870
Now. another $23. Now. $4. Now. $5.

364
00:21:28.954 --> 00:21:31.623
Garrett. I hear
your daughter's applying for A&M.

365
00:21:31.707 --> 00:21:34.584
If she wanna get in. you better
keep your goddamn hand down.

366
00:21:34.668 --> 00:21:36.628
[auctioneer] Can we go higher?

367
00:21:36.712 --> 00:21:38.672
And another $24 from Sam Kirkland.

368
00:21:38.755 --> 00:21:41.008
-Now. $5. And now…
-[Yancy] Boys.

369
00:21:41.091 --> 00:21:43.302
Yancy. Please tell me you're here to buy.

370
00:21:43.385 --> 00:21:45.262
Gotta offload a herd of Angus.

371
00:21:45.345 --> 00:21:47.014
[man] That's a shame.

372
00:21:47.097 --> 00:21:49.308
-How come?
-Because Sam Kirkland's how come.

373
00:21:49.391 --> 00:21:52.519
Rich prick needs a win to prove himself
to the Double K trustees.

374
00:21:52.602 --> 00:21:55.147
So. here he is.
strong-arming every rancher.

375
00:21:55.230 --> 00:21:58.108
promising back-end deals.
and undercutting every seller.

376
00:21:58.191 --> 00:22:00.610
[auctioneer] Any other takers?
Going once. going twice.

377
00:22:00.694 --> 00:22:04.448
and sold to Sam Kirkland
for 100 weight at $124.

378
00:22:09.870 --> 00:22:12.289
[Oliver] It's just like
walking through Brooklyn.

379
00:22:12.372 --> 00:22:13.373
[Quinn laughs]

380
00:22:13.457 --> 00:22:16.626
-Don't sass my town.
-I'm not sassing your town. I love it.

381
00:22:16.710 --> 00:22:20.005
It's just…
I can't believe that this place is real.

382
00:22:20.088 --> 00:22:22.257
Hm. Well. believe it.

383
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:23.800
[horse snorts]

384
00:22:23.884 --> 00:22:24.968
Hey. Davey.

385
00:22:25.469 --> 00:22:26.470
Quinn.

386
00:22:28.513 --> 00:22:31.266
This is Boone. Hey. Boone.

387
00:22:31.350 --> 00:22:34.519
That is without doubt
the coolest thing I've ever seen.

388
00:22:34.603 --> 00:22:35.687
Yeah.

389
00:22:36.396 --> 00:22:37.814
Is that the Maeve's?

390
00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:41.735
-[Quinn] Yeah.
-[Oliver] What happened to it?

391
00:22:43.653 --> 00:22:45.739
AWP happened to it.

392
00:22:47.532 --> 00:22:49.117
Tore up this whole town.

393
00:22:51.078 --> 00:22:55.874
Well. I think this place
is every bit as charming

394
00:22:55.957 --> 00:22:57.292
as you said it was.

395
00:22:57.376 --> 00:22:58.585
[Quinn chuckles]

396
00:22:58.668 --> 00:23:03.048
Yeah. maybe for now.
But… maybe my mom was right.

397
00:23:03.965 --> 00:23:05.008
About what?

398
00:23:05.717 --> 00:23:07.844
She wants to sell the farm.

399
00:23:07.928 --> 00:23:09.554
-What?
-Yeah.

400
00:23:10.389 --> 00:23:11.973
She wants to cash out.

401
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:15.936
She thinks this place is dying.

402
00:23:16.728 --> 00:23:17.938
And maybe it is.

403
00:23:18.021 --> 00:23:20.690
But what if I refused? Like…

404
00:23:22.526 --> 00:23:26.363
What if I refused to let her sell it?
I mean. like I just held out?

405
00:23:26.446 --> 00:23:29.783
Well. yeah. you could buy her out
and then take the money from the Phil.

406
00:23:29.866 --> 00:23:33.203
What? My money from the Phil
went to Gracie's.

407
00:23:34.496 --> 00:23:35.497
Hey…

408
00:23:40.085 --> 00:23:41.670
You're gonna figure this out.

409
00:23:43.588 --> 00:23:44.923
There was life here.

410
00:23:46.716 --> 00:23:49.469
And I got to figure out
how to bring it back

411
00:23:49.553 --> 00:23:51.388
before I do anything else.

412
00:23:56.184 --> 00:23:57.436
Can you be patient?

413
00:24:01.022 --> 00:24:02.899
-For you?
-Mm-hm.

414
00:24:04.985 --> 00:24:05.985
Yeah.

415
00:24:06.445 --> 00:24:07.529
Always.

416
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:18.373
[auctioneer] You don't see this
every day. a rarity here.

417
00:24:18.457 --> 00:24:21.918
We've got a whopping 96 fabulous
black Angus off the Fuller Ranch.

418
00:24:22.002 --> 00:24:25.172
represented now
by these four gorgeous animals.

419
00:24:25.255 --> 00:24:29.551
Averaging 525 pounds apiece.
who will start me off at 350?

420
00:24:30.343 --> 00:24:35.599
And 350. wasting no time. Sam K
with 350 a pop. looking now for 351.

421
00:24:35.682 --> 00:24:38.435
And 350. going to the end. 350 now. one.

422
00:24:39.561 --> 00:24:42.314
-Take a look at them premium steers.
-Come on.

423
00:24:42.397 --> 00:24:44.524
[auctioneer] How about you. Garrett?

424
00:24:44.608 --> 00:24:46.985
No other takers? No other takers?

425
00:24:47.527 --> 00:24:49.613
350 is where we stay. No other offers.

426
00:24:49.696 --> 00:24:52.032
This beautiful lot
will get over to Sam Kirkland.

427
00:24:52.115 --> 00:24:54.993
-[Yancy sighs]
-Going once. going twice. and…

428
00:24:55.076 --> 00:24:57.078
Hey now. 351.

429
00:24:57.162 --> 00:24:58.705
Another Kirkland has entered the game.

430
00:24:58.788 --> 00:25:01.875
That's bullshit! Double K has already bid!

431
00:25:01.958 --> 00:25:05.754
No. you're Double K. I'm just
an interested third party buyer.

432
00:25:05.837 --> 00:25:07.255
Oh. come on. Doug.

433
00:25:07.339 --> 00:25:11.718
[auctioneer] Unless Mr. Grey objects.
Staten is correct. the bidding continues.

434
00:25:11.801 --> 00:25:15.597
351 from Staten Kirkland.
352 from the Double K.

435
00:25:15.680 --> 00:25:19.476
Staten with 353. by goll.
Do I hear 354.

436
00:25:19.559 --> 00:25:21.686
-Sam with 354.
-Don't chase me. son.

437
00:25:23.396 --> 00:25:25.732
-What are you doing?
-I'm buying your cows.

438
00:25:25.815 --> 00:25:28.652
I appreciate you juicing your pop.
but you're going to tank this.

439
00:25:28.735 --> 00:25:31.696
-He just bid 354. That's a real offer.
-So is this. [whistles]

440
00:25:31.780 --> 00:25:35.742
[auctioneer] 355 from Staten.
Do I hear 356?

441
00:25:35.825 --> 00:25:38.078
And 356 from Sam Kirkland.

442
00:25:38.161 --> 00:25:40.205
I'll walk. Yancy. I will.

443
00:25:40.789 --> 00:25:42.707
356 is where I stop.

444
00:25:43.208 --> 00:25:44.376
It's final offer.

445
00:25:44.459 --> 00:25:46.545
-[auctioneer] Will Staten answer?
-I need that money.

446
00:25:46.628 --> 00:25:47.671
I know you do.

447
00:25:47.754 --> 00:25:50.590
[auctioneer] Waiting now.
but the steam is fading. folks.

448
00:25:50.674 --> 00:25:52.509
356 might do it.

449
00:25:52.592 --> 00:25:55.595
Going once. going twice. and…

450
00:25:55.679 --> 00:25:58.306
357 for Staten Kirkland!

451
00:25:59.766 --> 00:26:02.060
Going once. going twice. and

452
00:26:02.811 --> 00:26:05.689
sold for 357 to Staten Kirkland.

453
00:26:05.772 --> 00:26:09.568
Don't go anywhere. We'll have the next
lots lined up and ready in just a few.

454
00:26:09.651 --> 00:26:12.904
-Pay you back.
-No. You keep it. The cows. too.

455
00:26:13.905 --> 00:26:16.825
What… Look. I know you wanted
to give the guy the finger. but...

456
00:26:16.908 --> 00:26:18.743
I did. And I did.

457
00:26:20.537 --> 00:26:22.455
That was for you. Yance. And Ellie.

458
00:26:23.081 --> 00:26:24.124
All right?

459
00:26:24.916 --> 00:26:28.420
Fuller Ranch will not fall.
and neither will mine. You understand?

460
00:26:29.296 --> 00:26:30.964
We need each other to survive.

461
00:26:31.965 --> 00:26:36.678
My old man would never understand that.
but Cap… Cap understood that.

462
00:26:36.761 --> 00:26:39.180
[contemplative music playing]

463
00:26:39.264 --> 00:26:41.641
And I say we just keep the spirit alive.

464
00:26:42.559 --> 00:26:43.643
Yeah?

465
00:26:49.149 --> 00:26:50.233
Hey.

466
00:26:50.317 --> 00:26:51.735
[music fades]

467
00:26:53.236 --> 00:26:56.072
-Think you're pretty smart. don't you?
-Nah.

468
00:26:56.823 --> 00:26:59.075
Nah. I'm dumber
than a stack of shit-house bricks.

469
00:26:59.159 --> 00:27:01.244
I must get it from my father's side.

470
00:27:01.953 --> 00:27:05.540
-I told you not to come.
-And I told you to leave the kid alone.

471
00:27:06.207 --> 00:27:09.961
You must be happy with yourself.
Wasting good money to make a point?

472
00:27:10.045 --> 00:27:12.255
-Yeah. well. I got plenty of it.
-Mm.

473
00:27:12.339 --> 00:27:14.799
Figured I'd. I don't know. find a hobby.

474
00:27:15.508 --> 00:27:17.302
Yeah. [snickers]

475
00:27:17.385 --> 00:27:20.513
[bluesy rock music playing]

476
00:27:26.728 --> 00:27:28.605
Thought Double K had plenty of guys.

477
00:27:28.688 --> 00:27:33.401
We do. for now. Sam's looking
to grow the footprint by a mile.

478
00:27:33.485 --> 00:27:37.322
He's big on loyalty. Wants hands he can
count on. he's willing to pay for it.

479
00:27:37.947 --> 00:27:39.616
I came to y'all boys first.

480
00:27:43.370 --> 00:27:44.371
Think it over.

481
00:27:45.080 --> 00:27:48.583
Anyone interested
can find me at the Double K.

482
00:27:49.959 --> 00:27:51.920
Get you another one of those?

483
00:27:52.003 --> 00:27:53.630
Uh. no. I'm okay. thanks.

484
00:27:53.713 --> 00:27:57.467
You sure? You got to do something
to turn that frown upside down.

485
00:27:58.927 --> 00:27:59.928
I'm Tony.

486
00:28:03.056 --> 00:28:04.099
Hey. babe.

487
00:28:05.058 --> 00:28:06.101
Sorry I'm late.

488
00:28:08.728 --> 00:28:10.605
[Tony sighs]

489
00:28:14.567 --> 00:28:15.694
Thanks for that.

490
00:28:17.445 --> 00:28:18.822
What are you doing here?

491
00:28:19.739 --> 00:28:21.658
[sighs] It beat seeing my mom today.

492
00:28:22.450 --> 00:28:23.450
You went?

493
00:28:24.452 --> 00:28:28.373
I tried. but couldn't even make it
past the visitor's gate.

494
00:28:28.456 --> 00:28:29.457
[chuckles]

495
00:28:29.958 --> 00:28:31.251
Swing and a miss.

496
00:28:31.751 --> 00:28:33.128
Maybe we should get you...

497
00:28:33.211 --> 00:28:35.004
I just sat outside and I…

498
00:28:35.922 --> 00:28:39.467
Just I couldn't get over
how mad I still was. But…

499
00:28:40.844 --> 00:28:43.888
Then I just felt awful for her. Like…

500
00:28:44.597 --> 00:28:47.684
Feeling suffocated for so long.

501
00:28:50.645 --> 00:28:52.731
Life is strange. Isn't it?

502
00:28:52.814 --> 00:28:53.815
Yeah.

503
00:28:55.024 --> 00:28:56.025
Yeah. it is.

504
00:28:57.444 --> 00:28:59.404
[pool balls clatter]

505
00:28:59.487 --> 00:29:00.739
You like pool?

506
00:29:03.533 --> 00:29:06.453
[lively bluegrass music playing]

507
00:29:18.173 --> 00:29:19.424
Fitting right in.

508
00:29:20.633 --> 00:29:22.343
Yeah. he does have a knack.

509
00:29:24.345 --> 00:29:25.680
What am I going to do?

510
00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:30.518
I think you're just going to have
to follow your heart on this one.

511
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:31.686
[Quinn] Ah.

512
00:29:52.290 --> 00:29:54.042
Hey. license to kill on this thing?

513
00:29:54.125 --> 00:29:55.251
Yeah. go for it.

514
00:29:56.294 --> 00:29:58.421
All right. fool. step aside. It's go time.

515
00:29:58.505 --> 00:29:59.505
Go time?

516
00:29:59.547 --> 00:30:01.382
D… Did I stutter? Yeah.

517
00:30:01.466 --> 00:30:03.927
["I Fear You" by Tom Rhodes playing]

518
00:30:10.308 --> 00:30:11.434
Excuse me.

519
00:30:24.239 --> 00:30:25.532
Holy shit.

520
00:30:25.615 --> 00:30:27.909
All right. pay up. sucker.
I want my money.

521
00:30:29.536 --> 00:30:30.703
Thank you.

522
00:30:32.622 --> 00:30:33.748
We had a bet.

523
00:30:33.832 --> 00:30:36.459
-But a fair bet.
-Yeah. I just fairly whooped your ass.

524
00:30:36.543 --> 00:30:38.795
I don't think your shoulder's fucked.

525
00:30:39.587 --> 00:30:40.672
-What?
-Yeah.

526
00:30:40.755 --> 00:30:43.216
I think you're. uh. you're faking it.
A pool shark thing.

527
00:30:43.299 --> 00:30:46.135
Oh my god. you're ridiculous.
Give me my money.

528
00:30:46.219 --> 00:30:48.596
-No. medical records. I want proof.
-Stop! [chuckles]

529
00:30:48.680 --> 00:30:51.850
-You're being a sore loser. Stop.
-Then don't be a liar.

530
00:30:55.019 --> 00:30:58.857
♪ I fear you. oh ♪

531
00:30:59.357 --> 00:31:01.484
♪ I fear you ♪

532
00:31:03.945 --> 00:31:08.199
♪ I fear you. oh ♪

533
00:31:08.283 --> 00:31:10.410
♪ I fear you ♪

534
00:31:15.290 --> 00:31:17.208
Wait. So this clown walks in…

535
00:31:17.292 --> 00:31:19.836
Yeah. So the clown walks in.

536
00:31:19.919 --> 00:31:22.005
Very last minute.
mind you. super dramatic.

537
00:31:22.088 --> 00:31:25.633
Every head turns. and he starts
a bidding war with his old man.

538
00:31:25.717 --> 00:31:26.593
Jesus. Staten.

539
00:31:26.676 --> 00:31:29.929
And then he bids $357.
and I swear to God.

540
00:31:30.013 --> 00:31:32.307
I thought his old man's head
was going to pop.

541
00:31:32.390 --> 00:31:34.100
No. that's just his head.

542
00:31:34.684 --> 00:31:35.727
Well. shit.

543
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:39.647
I'm glad it worked out.
but I'm calling it. fellas.

544
00:31:39.731 --> 00:31:43.192
No. Dan. stay a beer. Yancy's buying.
He's flush with cash.

545
00:31:43.276 --> 00:31:45.153
-Yeah. come on.
-It's all right.

546
00:31:45.236 --> 00:31:47.238
There are a lot of girls around here.

547
00:31:47.322 --> 00:31:49.782
Yeah. well. that there are.

548
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:54.412
You know. I heard
that Derek and Angie are separated.

549
00:31:54.495 --> 00:31:56.998
As I recall. you and Angie
had a bit of a history.

550
00:31:57.832 --> 00:31:59.834
-Huh? I don't mean to overstep.
-Yeah.

551
00:31:59.918 --> 00:32:02.754
Well. then don't. I'll see you. boys.

552
00:32:03.338 --> 00:32:05.173
-All right.
-You. uh. watch for deer.

553
00:32:07.884 --> 00:32:11.387
Just needs a little push. is all.
Come on. let's get a beer.

554
00:32:16.434 --> 00:32:19.103
Hey. can I get two more beers. please?
Thank you.

555
00:32:27.779 --> 00:32:30.239
-Where's all that stand?
-[bartender] Here you go.

556
00:32:30.323 --> 00:32:31.324
Ah. it doesn't.

557
00:32:32.951 --> 00:32:34.285
I've been kneecapped.

558
00:32:35.828 --> 00:32:39.707
I've been kneecapped for six months.
You showed up and you fought for me.

559
00:32:39.791 --> 00:32:43.544
'Cause that's what you do.
You fight. For what's important.

560
00:32:45.129 --> 00:32:46.172
What you love.

561
00:32:47.256 --> 00:32:49.926
Shit. man.
Take me to dinner first. would you?

562
00:32:53.262 --> 00:32:55.640
I think we were wrong about that land.

563
00:32:55.723 --> 00:32:58.226
I don't believe Cap made a bad call.

564
00:32:58.309 --> 00:32:59.435
Why's that?

565
00:33:00.645 --> 00:33:02.480
He invested in you. didn't he?

566
00:33:05.233 --> 00:33:09.487
My granddad said you can find value
in any land. you just got to look for it.

567
00:33:11.864 --> 00:33:13.825
You've got to keep fighting. kid.

568
00:33:15.326 --> 00:33:16.911
It ain't just you anymore.

569
00:33:19.455 --> 00:33:21.374
All right. I got to take a piss.

570
00:33:34.345 --> 00:33:35.471
Holy shit.

571
00:33:39.767 --> 00:33:41.978
Hey. hey! I know how to get rid of her.

572
00:33:42.061 --> 00:33:43.146
How?

573
00:33:43.229 --> 00:33:46.024
-You're not going to like it.
-Yeah? Try me.

574
00:33:51.195 --> 00:33:53.197
Oh! Sorry.

575
00:33:53.781 --> 00:33:54.991
Um… Oliver.

576
00:33:55.908 --> 00:33:56.909
Staten Kirkland.

577
00:33:57.952 --> 00:33:59.203
The Staten Kirkland?

578
00:33:59.871 --> 00:34:00.747
Yeah.

579
00:34:00.830 --> 00:34:02.123
I've heard a lot about you.

580
00:34:02.707 --> 00:34:05.585
That's funny.
I've never heard anything about you.

581
00:34:07.962 --> 00:34:08.962
Okay.

582
00:34:13.426 --> 00:34:14.510
-Hey.
-Hey.

583
00:34:16.846 --> 00:34:19.557
-You sound good out there.
-Nah. it was the band.

584
00:34:19.640 --> 00:34:21.184
They were amazing. honestly.

585
00:34:21.267 --> 00:34:23.269
-They just played "Crested Hens".
-Hm.

586
00:34:23.352 --> 00:34:25.897
-Nobody knows that song.
-Ransom doesn't mess around.

587
00:34:25.980 --> 00:34:27.899
Babe. I'm telling you. this place.

588
00:34:27.982 --> 00:34:30.818
and then the stories
that the guys were telling me.

589
00:34:30.902 --> 00:34:33.780
-Johnny Cash? You kidding me?
-What'd they tell you?

590
00:34:34.697 --> 00:34:38.993
That he was passing through town in '68
when his tour bus breaks down.

591
00:34:39.869 --> 00:34:41.370
And so. what does he do?

592
00:34:42.288 --> 00:34:46.042
He sets up shop and plays for three days
straight while they fix the bus.

593
00:34:46.125 --> 00:34:49.921
Not just that. he played here. When
this place was some old oil factory.

594
00:34:50.004 --> 00:34:52.965
-Wow.
-Then his friends started piling in too.

595
00:34:53.049 --> 00:34:57.845
Arlo. Waylon. Townes.
Willie freaking Nelson.

596
00:34:59.806 --> 00:35:02.016
People came from all over to listen.

597
00:35:04.811 --> 00:35:06.604
This place was a destination.

598
00:35:09.565 --> 00:35:10.900
There was magic here.

599
00:35:13.027 --> 00:35:14.570
[sighs]

600
00:35:14.654 --> 00:35:16.614
There is still magic here.

601
00:35:18.282 --> 00:35:19.909
You thinking what I'm thinking?

602
00:35:20.910 --> 00:35:22.328
I think I am.

603
00:35:32.672 --> 00:35:35.007
[Lauren] Hey. it's Lauren.
Leave a message.

604
00:35:39.720 --> 00:35:40.972
[sighs]

605
00:35:42.932 --> 00:35:44.308
[door opens]

606
00:35:46.269 --> 00:35:47.562
[door closes]

607
00:35:53.192 --> 00:35:55.403
[melancholic music playing]

608
00:35:56.154 --> 00:35:57.530
[door closes]

609
00:35:59.407 --> 00:36:00.908
[object clatters on counter]

610
00:36:15.339 --> 00:36:17.258
[music fades]

611
00:36:22.013 --> 00:36:24.348
Looks like someone's
drinking to something.

612
00:36:24.974 --> 00:36:25.975
I am.

613
00:36:27.518 --> 00:36:28.686
Grab a glass.

614
00:36:29.770 --> 00:36:31.647
It depends what we're drinking to.

615
00:36:33.107 --> 00:36:34.400
[chuckles]

616
00:36:35.735 --> 00:36:37.445
My million-dollar idea.

617
00:36:42.200 --> 00:36:43.784
[Quinn chuckles]

618
00:36:45.953 --> 00:36:48.331
-Edge of my seat here. Quinn.
-All right.

619
00:36:48.414 --> 00:36:51.209
The town's disappearing
right before my eyes.

620
00:36:52.627 --> 00:36:54.462
My mom's trying to sell my farm.

621
00:36:54.545 --> 00:36:56.088
Well. I know the feeling.

622
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:59.550
And… I'm gonna save it.

623
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:04.597
Gracie's was born out of a random
jam session just like that one.

624
00:37:04.680 --> 00:37:07.141
The greats played here once. they're…

625
00:37:07.642 --> 00:37:09.435
They're gonna play here again.

626
00:37:12.688 --> 00:37:15.107
I'm gonna throw a music festival.

627
00:37:15.191 --> 00:37:16.317
Right here.

628
00:37:16.400 --> 00:37:18.569
And it's gonna be ongoing.

629
00:37:18.653 --> 00:37:22.198
and it's gonna fuel this town
financially for years to come.

630
00:37:24.659 --> 00:37:27.286
Know what I'm gonna do
with the first money that comes in?

631
00:37:28.162 --> 00:37:29.538
Gonna buy back the farm.

632
00:37:30.122 --> 00:37:32.541
I'm gonna buy back my sweet little farm.

633
00:37:32.625 --> 00:37:34.418
[chuckling] I like it.

634
00:37:35.002 --> 00:37:37.088
I mean. it's just a seed. but you know.

635
00:37:37.171 --> 00:37:40.049
Hey. a hundred-year oak was just a seed.

636
00:37:47.098 --> 00:37:49.267
-I'm sorry about yesterday at the diner.
-No.

637
00:37:50.226 --> 00:37:53.312
-You don't have to do that.
-No. no. I do.

638
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:54.522
I was an asshole.

639
00:37:55.898 --> 00:37:57.191
You were right.

640
00:37:58.776 --> 00:38:01.487
I can't change the past.
but I can change the future.

641
00:38:01.570 --> 00:38:03.990
-Staten!
-Did you say yes?

642
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:09.912
No. I didn't say yes.

643
00:38:11.163 --> 00:38:13.541
I have to build a music festival
from the ground up.

644
00:38:13.624 --> 00:38:16.335
and I'd like to focus on that right now.

645
00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:18.504
Good.

646
00:38:19.213 --> 00:38:20.339
Good?

647
00:38:21.424 --> 00:38:22.925
I got a little time.

648
00:38:24.802 --> 00:38:26.137
To the music festival.

649
00:38:27.471 --> 00:38:29.849
Yeah. of course. to the music festival.

650
00:38:32.601 --> 00:38:34.312
[sighs]

651
00:38:40.568 --> 00:38:41.569
Lovely.

652
00:38:43.237 --> 00:38:45.197
This where you're hiding my body?

653
00:38:45.281 --> 00:38:48.159
You and I are gonna pull a job.
One more for the road.

654
00:38:48.993 --> 00:38:49.994
Are we now?

655
00:38:50.077 --> 00:38:51.579
[intriguing music playing]

656
00:38:51.662 --> 00:38:52.663
On who?

657
00:38:54.123 --> 00:38:55.124
Sam Kirkland.

658
00:38:56.542 --> 00:38:59.378
He's got a gambler's heart
and cash to spend. I know it.

659
00:38:59.462 --> 00:39:01.714
He's ripe for the take.
so we're gonna take him.

660
00:39:01.797 --> 00:39:02.798
How?

661
00:39:02.882 --> 00:39:03.883
Oil.

662
00:39:04.383 --> 00:39:07.178
We convince him there's black gold
on this useless land.

663
00:39:07.261 --> 00:39:11.223
Reel him in. run the price.
take him for a massive score.

664
00:39:11.807 --> 00:39:14.268
We could pocket the whole thing.
I keep my ranch. and...

665
00:39:14.352 --> 00:39:15.936
I'll give you your divorce.

666
00:39:17.146 --> 00:39:18.189
Sam Kirkland…

667
00:39:20.232 --> 00:39:21.609
That is a big fish.

668
00:39:24.070 --> 00:39:27.948
Yancy. darling. I just fleeced you.
textbook "Bird in the Hand."

669
00:39:28.032 --> 00:39:30.910
I'm not about to pull some harebrained
scheme for a little cash.

670
00:39:33.454 --> 00:39:34.705
Yeah. you are.

671
00:39:36.791 --> 00:39:37.833
And why is that?

672
00:39:39.668 --> 00:39:42.088
Because I know you… darling.

673
00:39:43.506 --> 00:39:45.132
And I know you can't resist.

674
00:39:53.766 --> 00:39:55.768
[music fades]

675
00:39:57.395 --> 00:39:59.814
[gentle upbeat music playing]

676
00:42:39.557 --> 00:42:41.725
[music fades]

676
